<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="693" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1477a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-20T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 20,
                                            1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Report by telegram in what respects and to what degree Russian
                                functions in regard to (1) actual control of the Chinese Eastern
                                Railway and (2) municipal administration in railway zone have been
                                taken over by Chinese or other non-Russian agencies.</p>
                            <p>Department desires not only a general view of the situation but also
                                specific instances in brief for its information. Make reply complete
                                but avoid unnecessary length.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>